-- U.S. crude futures drop more than $3/bbl
-- 
-- Mon Aug 6, 2007 2:37pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/06/us-energy-nymex-crude-idUSN0641707120070806

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - U.S. crude oil futures fell sharply on Monday, dropping more than $3, as jitters about slowing economic growth pressured crude oil and RBOB gasoline and heating oil futures. 

 On the New York Mercantile Exchange at 2:11 p.m. EDT (1611 GMT), September crude CLU7 was down $2.98, or 3.95 percent, at $72.50 a barrel, trading from $72.40 to $75.10.